<center><strong>CHARACTERISTICS OF THE "A" CATEGORY<br /><br />OUTDOOR</strong></center>
<p>If you have a high score in category “A,” you will probably prefer outdoor-related jobs. “Outdoor” has to do with work that involves tending and managing the environment. You are likely to be an active person who enjoys physical activities. You would enjoy a job where you can work with your hands building and repairing things. You are a practical person who appreciates nature. People with outdoor-related jobs are very important to society because they help preserve our environment. (Previous versions of the Interest Inventory before 2003 call this category “Agriculture/Forestry.”)</p>
